g. Large corporations, non-bank financial institutions, governments, and bank clients are all evolving their own client relationships with increased direct selling, alternative payment channels, broader currency reach, tokenized cash, wallets etc. These changes must be aligned in context with a highly complex legal, regulatory, technological, market, and tax environments governing J.P. Morgan. Integrating these new disruptive technologies into our environment successfully will be key to our continued growth and increased relevance in the markets we serve. Role & Responsibilities The Liquidity & Escrow Services Product & Business Development Manager will develop relationships across the Wholesale Payments organization to identify and articulate business or product opportunities arising from product/industry gaps, customer needs and regulatory and/or technology developments. They will support Senior management to prioritize promising ideas based on commercial criteria and partner with JPM technology, legal, compliance, tax, operations, and treasury and client coverage teams to execute them and drive revenue. Develop rich understanding of the Wholesale Liquidity & Escrow product suite, including drivers of revenue, capabilities relative to industry/customer needs and current business priorities Maintain dialogue with senior managers across Liquidity & Escrow product and client coverage teams on emerging customer needs and product opportunities; including supporting consultative client dialogue on new opportunities Work with senior managers to articulate & flesh out novel ideas that can transform the business and enhance client relationships & compliment the broader business strategy Assess the operational and commercial viability of promising ideas \u2013 in particular developing commercially sound use cases and business economics Structure new products and services through creative usage of pricing, customer integration/interaction models (e.g. API\u2019s), existing Wholesale Payments capabilities, emerging technologies (e.g. Blockchain) and enhancements to core technology capabilities Build relationships across functional partners including legal, tax, compliance and JPM treasury to efficiently identify regulatory/funding constraints and validate new product concepts Partner with above teams to champion the approval of new products and services though JPM\u2019s New Products/Business approval processes Oversee delivery of specific programs & capabilities; manage portion of team\u2019s product delivery portfolio Background And Skill Requirements Bachelor\u2019s degree with 10 years of professional experience Strong analytical mindset with very strong attention to detail Creative & innovative thinker who is able to structure \u2018non-traditional\u2019 solutions to meet business/customer needs Superior written and verbal communication skills, including ability to communicate complex ideas coherently for senior executive and client audiences Ability to develop strong relationships across functions and seniority levels in a large matrix organization; ability to effectively influence partners outside their reporting hierarchy Experience in managing juniors and/or a team Proven track record of delivering complex programs and/or new products in a large financial services organization; Highly organized with strong execution bias Ability to travel internationally Experience/Knowledge of one or more of the following: Core transaction banking services covering wholesale clients Financial regulations affecting liquidity and/or transaction banking services Interest rate and money markets businesses Corporate or Bank Treasury, Liability/Liquidity planning and /or ALM ",
